==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Ravelin
<hw>Rave"lin</hw> <pr>(r⟦acr⟧v"l⟦icr⟧n; 277)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[F.; cf. Sp. <ets>rebellin</ets>, It. <ets>revellino</ets>,
<ets>rivellino</ets>; perhaps fr. L. <ets>re-</ets> again +
<ets>vallum</ets> wall.]</ety> <fld>(Fort.)</fld> <def>A detached work
with two embankments which make a salient angle. It is raised before the
curtain on the counterscarp of the place. Formerly called
<altname>demilune</altname> and <altname>half-moon</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Raveling</ent>⟦br⟧
